<plot>Honolulu city council forgets to read the first amendment to the Constitution and tries to pass a law banning street performers in a four block area of Waikiki. The Mayor steps in to veto the bill and all hell breaks lose. To add to the controversy mimes talk and business owners can't seem to find the right words. Roger Wilko takes you on a fun ride.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?362310</url></doc>
